==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stearic
<hw>Ste*ar"ic</hw> <pr>(st⟦esl⟧*⟦acr⟧r"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>st⟦eacute⟧arique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or obtained from, stearin or tallow;
resembling tallow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stearic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
monobasic fatty acid, obtained in the form of white crystalline scales,
soluble in alcohol and ether. It melts to an oily liquid at
69⟦deg⟧C.</cd></cs><-- b.p. 383⟦deg⟧. <chform>C18H36O2</chform>,
<chform>CH3.(CH2)16.COOH</chform>; sodium stearate, with sodium
palmitate, is the main component of ordinary bar soaps (Such as Ivory
soap). -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stearin</ent>⟦br⟧
